description:
From the company that brings you nothing but good chicken, Gold'n Plump is now offering all the goodness of chicken in chef-inspired sausages.

Gold’n Plump Italian Cheese & Peppers fully-cooked chicken sausages are made with premium-quality, boneless skinless thigh meat, from chickens that have been raised with no antibiotics-ever combined with Aged Parmesan & Asiago cheeses, Red & Green Peppers and flavorful spices. Plus, the sausages are free of monosodium glutamate (MSG), fillers, nitrates/nitrites, gluten and artificial flavors and colors . At 15gm of protein and 72% less fat than pork sausage*, Gold'n Plump Italian Cheese & Peppers chicken sausage offers chef-inspired flavored with less guilt.

Good Chicken is our Mission®

*7 g of fat per link compared to 25g of fat for pork sausage per USDA data

description:
All-natural (no artificial ingredients, minimally processed). Fully cooked. Inspected for wholesomeness by US Department of Agriculture. Quick-peel. Tear one off and the rest stay fresh! Single-peel. What is craft sausage? People ask us al the time what we mean by craft sausage. It means a commitment to staying small and independent, and a passion for flavor and quality. We create sausage not for the widest audience, but for the individual. If you want great new flavors without the fillers, sodium nitrite, or by-products, try a craft sausage for a change. Made with all-natural chicken and sauteed onions. If you're not totally satisfied with our sausage, let us know at GilbertsSausage. Happy eating! - Gilbert's. Proudly crafted in Wisconsin.

Directions:

Keep refrigerated or frozen. Fully cooked in package. Just warm and serve. Grill: Remove wrapper. Place on heated grill, turn frequently until grilled to taste. Microwave: Leave in wrapper. Place link in microwave (Microwave ovens vary, heating times are approximate) warm on high 20-25 seconds. Stovetop: Remove wrapper. Place link in hot water or saute, warm 3-4 minutes. Serving Suggestion - Served Sheboygan-style with pickles, onions and brown mustard.

Directions:

Keep refrigerated. Heating Instructions: Remove sausage from package. Stovetop: Place in pan and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Oven: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. Place in pan and add 1/2 inch water. Cover pan with lid or foil and heat for 15 minutes. Microwave: Place in microwaveable safe dish and cover. Heat for 1.5 to 2 minutes on high (or until desired temperature). Grill: Heat to desired temperature. It is recommended to heat to an internal temperature of 160 degrees F.
